    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I installed neovim on Ubuntu 15.04. It is generally really fast and recognized all the plugins immediately. However, I'm not sure the commands `:bn` and `:bp` are working correctly. This is what I do to reproduce the issue:\n1. nvim\n2. Type something in the current buffer: \"abc\"\n3.  `:vsplit`\n4. `<ctrl-w> <ctrl-w>` (to move to the recently created split)\n5. `:term`\n6. `:bp` (and this changes correctly the second split to the previous buffer containing \"abc\"\n7. `:bn` (which doesn't return to the terminal as it should)\n\nIf I use buffers that are not terminals, `:bn` and `:bp` work correctly, though.\n\nCan you reproduce this issue?\n",
