            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I'm able to reproduce the issue with the latest version\n\n```\nNVIM 0.0.0-alpha+201509121307 (compiled Sep 14 2015 09:48:07)\nCommit: 5c82ea8f9f9f3ef043d4f206ded223a89a3bd360\n```\n\nSeem like when `nohidden` is set and you use `:bn` or `:bp` so that the terminal buffer is no longer displayed within a window, it gets unloaded without warning.\n\n```\nnvim -u NONE ~/.nvimrc\n:term\n<c-\\><c-n>\n:ls\n:bp\n:ls\n# terminal buffer will now be unloaded\n```\n\nI'm unsure whether this is a bug or not since terminal buffers return  0 for `:echo &modified` so it is correct that they be unloaded when they are no longer displayed in a window.\n",
