            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Recap: there's at least 1 bug here: terminal buffers are removed from `:ls` when they are abandoned and `'nohidden'` is set. But there's an unanswered question about what we should do with terminal buffers for `'nohidden'`: \n- should we ignore `'nohidden'` and keep the terminal running (this is contrary to the normal operation of `'nohidden'`)?\n- should we just restart the shell when the terminal buffer is revisited?\n",
