        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I believe this cannot be solved by looking backwards. I think it's a really nice feature to have a terminal buffer that I'm able to interact with within nvim, but if the application running in it (an ssh session for instance, or some interactive console) may be killed because it's not in a window, it defeats at least the purpose I use it for. Restarting the shell would therefore also not be useful.\n\nI guess that people will use this differently, so configurability is probably the way forward. However, killing terminal sessions is not a desired default behaviour.\n",
