        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Personally I'm against making terminal buffers more special than needed. They should be treated like any other buffers.\n\nSo, when abandoning a buffer, and that's what happens when a buffer is not active (thus not visible) anymore, I expect it to get unloaded if `nohidden` is set.\n\nIf anything, we could talk about making `hidden` a default, but I'm sure that was a discussion before.\n",
