        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Should terminal buffers always be considered modified?  That resolves the issue of the buffer being abandoned when `'nohidden'` is set.  From Neovim's perspective, there's no knowledge of what's happening in the terminal so it can't know if the shell should be killed or not.\n\nBy having that buffer modified while the shell is running, it means the user has to make the choice about whether and how to kill the processes that are running.\n",
            "created_at": "2016-07-28T10:11:24Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/3340#issuecomment-235855050",
            "id": 235855050,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/3340",
