        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "A terminal buffer is something interactive and I like @jamessan's suggestion to just always assume `modified` (`nomodified` is hardcoded at the moment), so it throws an error when trying to switch. Then you either delete the terminal buffer or set `hidden`.\n\nThis also prevents the other open questions like \"_Should an unloaded terminal buffer get removed from the buffer list?_\" and \"_What to do when revisiting an unloaded buffer?_\".\n",
