        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Followup to https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/3340#issuecomment-192812245 : \r\n\r\n> there's at least 1 bug here: terminal buffers are removed from `:ls` when they are abandoned and `'nohidden'` is set. \r\n\r\nCan't reproduce that anymore. Though https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/6280 seems like a more proper fix.\r\n\r\n> what we should do with terminal buffers for `'nohidden'`: should we ignore `'nohidden'` and keep the terminal running (this is contrary to the normal operation of `'nohidden'`)?\r\n\r\nThat's still an open question.\r\n\r\nBut the main issue here appears to be resolved.",
